Garry sets the spool of wire down, removes his hat and examines the flashlight. He taps it
against his palm.

Behind him, Blair suddenly appears from out of nowhere.

Garry turns his head around. Blair reaches out with unnatural speed and grabs Garry's face with
his hand, smothering him instantly. Garry moans. Blair pushes Garry's head back up against a
wall. Garry is powerless.

Using tremendous strength, Blair forces his fingers deep under the
surface of the skin around Garry's mouth. Garry gags. He begins to lose consciousness. Blair
takes a look around him while Garry suffocates. Garry stops gurgling. He is still.


NAULS

continues stringing a line of detonating wire down the floor of the passageway. Several feet
behind him, MacReady kneels in the center of basement preparing the detonator. The men work
feverishly.

GARRY'S

body lies motionless on the floor, he is dragged away by a thick meaty sinew connecting his head
with Blair's arm.

NAULS

moves further into the narrow passageway laying the wire down. A noise. He freezes. Fear. He
stares deep into the shadows at the other end of the passageway. The sound of heavy breathing
followed by a low raspy growl. He goes to investigate, as if compelled to meet his fate.


MACREADY

kneels over the detonator, completing the final preparations. With his attention on the
detonator, MacReady calls out to the other men to see if they are finished.


MACREADY
How's it coming in there?


No response.

MACREADY
I said, how's it...


He freezes mid-sentence. He listens for a second then quickly removes his hood and turns his
attention to the corridor behind him. It is empty.

A beat.

MacReady slowly pulls up the plunger handle as he peers down the corridor. The only sound is the
dripping of water.

He stands up and slowly takes a few steps toward the corridor, the crunching of snow under his
feet. He stops at the entrance. Tense. Something is near. He ignites a lighter. In his other hand
he holds a stick of dynamite. He lights the fuse.

He waits.

A slight noise at the end of the corridor draws his attention. He freezes.

Old furniture, wooden crates and pallets are stacked upon each other and against the walls.

A beat.

Suddenly, the creaking of an old cabinet as it tips over, then something massive charges at
MacReady from under the floor. Thunderous noise. Wooden planks, snow and earth explode into the
air. The force propels MacReady against the wall. The stick of dynamite flies from his grip and
lands a few feet away. The fuse continues to burn.

Disoriented, MacReady lifts himself into a sitting position, he looks over to the detonator lying
on the ground.

The floor shakes. Hissing. A mass of thick tentacles suddenly bursts through the floor. They seek
out the detonator, grab it and pull it down into the hole.

A split second later, The Thing's massive torso explodes up through the floor, howling in fury.
Rattling. Hissing. Stunned, MacReady looks up at the creature.

At the top of the giant stalk-like body are flailing arms and claws, topped with a head featuring
a massive dinosaur-like jaw lined with large vicious canine teeth. The jaw is fused to the side
of a head resembling a grotesque imitation of Blair. The Thing opens it's jaws wide open and
emits a terrifying roar.


Flesh splits open along it's trunk-like abdomen, a deformed dog-like head squeezes out,
struggling to break free, biting madly into the air. Growling loudly.

MacReady scampers to his feet, grabs the stick of dynamite and leaps down into another section of
the basement. He rolls to his feet, stands up and looks back at the fearsome creature. He
prepares to throw the stick of dynamite. The creature roars again.


MACREADY
Yeah, fuck you too!


MacReady throws the stick of dynamite at the creature. It lands at the foot of the creature. The
dog-like head looks down at the explosive, it lets out terrifying screeching howl. Kaboom! The
dynamite detonates.

An immense explosion sends a fireball fifty feet into the sky. The Thing's
body disintegrating almost immediately.

The explosion sets off a chain reaction as the other bundles of dynamite ignite and the entire
camp is leveled to the ground. The Thing's screaming and roaring echo through the night air, then
falls silent. Explosions continue to rock the compound for a moment longer. The destroyed
buildings lie in shambles and on fire.

CUT TO:

INT. CAMP

A ruin. Almost to the ground. Fires burning across the compound.

MacReady wears a thick blanket which covers him like a shroud, from his shoulders to the floor.
He walks bent over and in much pain. Bottle of whiskey in hand.

Looking for shelter, he limps into the remains of a building lying in shambles. He finds a place
on the ground to rest. He leans up against the wall and brings the bottle up to his lips.

Childs enters the frame and whirls a startled MacReady around.

Childs stands before him, holding a torch, pointed at him. He looks as weak as MacReady. A beat.


CHILDS
You the only one who made it?


MACREADY
[suspicious]
Not the only one.


The fires crackle loudly around the men.


CHILDS
Did you kill it.


MACREADY
Where were you, Childs?


CHILDS
I thought I saw Blair...I went out after him
and got lost in the storm.


MacReady chuckles. Childs steps back, keeping his distance and painfully sits down across from
MacReady.


CHILDS
Fire's got the temperature up all over
the camp...won't last long though.


MACREADY
Neither will we.


CHILDS
How will we make it?


MACREADY
Maybe we shouldn't.


The two men continue to eye each other.


CHILDS
If you're worried about me...

MACREADY
[cuts in]
If we've got any surprises for each
other...I don't think we're in much
shape to do anything about it.


CHILDS
Well...what do we do?


MACREADY
Why don't we just...wait here for a
little while? See what happens.


They regard each other for a moment.

MacReady grins and hands the bottle to Childs. Childs smiles back and takes a healthy swig.

They both chuckle.

EXT. COMPOUND - NIGHT

The fires smolder on. Bright embers dance in the blackness -- pushed by the soughing wind.

FADE OUT.

THE END
